Use of latest technologies, such as the Internet, to enhance the government services to the public in the United Kingdom has been underpinned by the British governmentâ€™s emphasis of several key e-initiatives, including e-policing and integration of criminal justice IT (CJIT) systems. This paper presents an overview of several on-going and planned system integration and re-engineering programmes in the Police Service and CJIT in the UK using XML & Web Services, as well as key findings and lessons learnt from undertaking these programmes.